  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Civil society capacity building in Northern Kosovo via Slovak Balkan Public Policy Fund</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Main objectives of the program are creation of a functioning network between Northern Kosovo municipalities, state institutions, donors and civil society, and activization of the donor community in the Northern Kosovo context of specific civil society issues.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at intensifying cooperation with civil society in the Northern Kosovo municipalities based on previous experience of the Slovak Balkan Public Policy Fund. The program implies assignment of six small grants for local projects, conduction of trainings for local activists (both individuals and local NGOs). An important part of the program are study visits to Slovakia for some of the participants to further strengthen the cooperation and to enhance more effective share of Slovak experience in building active civil society.</narrative>
  </description>
